I’m not sure how “unique” most of these idols would be considered by others, but they’re the ones who I can immediately recognize where ever they are. I see a lot of people answering this with idols who don’t necessarily fit Korea’s beauty standards, but I guess I’m approaching the question a little differently? So yeah. When I start stanning groups, there’s usually a few members I learn the names of first since I find them instantly recognizeable. When I start stanning a new group it usually takes me a little bit to match all the faces to the names, but usually a few members jump out at me immediately and I can pick them out instantly. Here’s a few examples. Blackpink was the first group I ever stanned, and the member that I could always recognize was Lisa. With NCT, as with most people, I immediately noticed Taeyong. Part of that is definitely due to his stage presence and the fact that he’s usually in the center, but his face is very recognizable in my opinon. I also usually notice Vernon from Seventeen, even though I don’t even stan them, something about Vernon always jumps out at me. Hwasa from Mamamoo is pretty unique in my opinion, she’s one of the idols who really doesn’t fit Korea’s beauty standards, but it just makes her stand out more in my opinion. The first member I noticed in Stray Kids was Felix- the best way I can think of to describe it is that he has very delicate features? idk, they’re almost fairy-like. (also, JYPE needs to stop covering up his freckles) I also think Yeji from Itzy has pretty unique features. Idk how to describe it, and I don’t even know how actually unique they are, but to me at least she stands out.

response.answer_text: These idols stood out to me when I first got introduced to their groups. I found their looks unique and not-so-common in the Kpop industry. Many of them even ended up being my bias/bias wreckers in that group❤❤ (NOTE: >I am clearly not judging them by their looks. It’s just that they stood out to me….maybe because of their facial features. ) RM- BTS  BTS was the first Kpop group I ever stanned. I got to know them through a friend. When I first searched them up, RM totally stood out to me. He looked very professional and somehow reminded me of my math sir (Idk why lol😂). His dimples added that extra uniqueness to his face. RM gave off that “Leader” vibes. I was totally not surprised when I came to know that he was actually the leader of BTS. 2. Siwon- Super Junior  I feel that he’s very similar to RM. Looks very professional and organized. I would have never guessed that he was an idol. In the first pic I saw of Suju, I literally thought he was their manager 😂. Overall he gave me a “Rich CEO on vacation” vibe. (Btw he’s now one of my bias wreckers❤) 3. Johnny- NCT  Tbh, his visuals never really struck me. I didn’t think anything special about it. He was……umm…..kinda ok to me. But the more I looked at him, the more I realised how unique his looks were. His visuals literally grew on me (If that makes sense😂). Rn he is one of my bias wreckers in NCT 127. Ig he will one day end up being my bias too. 4. N- Vixx  I first saw him in a drama and didn’t even realise that he was an idol. Not until I heard him sing one of the OSTs. I really loved his voice and decided to search him up. I came to know that he was from a group named VIXX. He really stood out to me in every MV of theirs. I got to say……his visuals……totally…..hits differently❤❤ 5. Amber Liu  Ahhhhhh……My girl crush❤❤❤❤. I totally fell for both her looks and her personality. I just love how she’s confident and just being herself❤❤ 6. Jeno- NCT  This sounds sooo wrong…..but I felt his visuals were a bit intimidating in the beginning (That feeling vanished into thin air after I saw his smile tho❤❤). He has a very masculine appearance. I somehow thought he would have a strict personality. But oh myyy…..can I be more mistaken?? He is one of the softest fluffball in the whole Kpop industry (Certainly NOT when he’s on stage😂) 7. Sehun- EXO   So….there is an embarrassing reason as to why I put 2 of sehun’s pics. I think EXO was the second group I stanned. I watched many videos and MVs. Then at last….I decided to check out a ‘Guide to EXO” video. That’s when I realised how stupid I had been. I literally thought the SMILING sehun and the NOT-SMILING sehun were two entirely different people. I then understood why I couldn’t find the SMILING sehun in the MVs (Im cringing soooo hard at myself rn😂). He looked like two different people to me. Ahhhhhh……I BET I WILL NEVER FORGET THIS EMBARRASSING MISUNDERSTANDING That’s it for now guys…. I’ll add more names when I remember them❤❤

Unique? Hm. By that, I understand that their visuals are unconventional or not similar to other idols' visuals. So here are a few idols who I find unique looking: ITZY’s Chaeryoung Even though she gets a lot for her visuals I find her beautiful and unique looking. All of ITZY members have beautiful visuals, but Chaeryoung stands out a lot. Though a lot of times I do not think styling does her visuals justice (the other members too!! Ahh wish their styling would change haha)  (^^she looks absolutely stunning non-whitewashed)   Nana She was mentioned in a forum and I haven’t heard of her before so when I searched her I was stunned by her visuals. I have never seen a K-Pop idol have these types of visuals and I was in awe. I am not sure how unique her look is in the acting world and in Korea, but to me, I can’t find visuals like her in K-pop now. Her visuals look very natural to me (Also Chaeryoung’s visuals) and I wish this type of visual would become trendy again!!!    Red Velvet’s Seulgi I myself am a “Goddess=Irene” person, I am not oblivious to Seulgi’s unique and stunning visuals. (Seulrene Visual couple!!!!) It’s her traditional monolid eyes that give her that unique aura, I believe. They suit her very well and also give her an edge, too.    BTS’ RM When I first got into BTS RM was the first member that caught my eyes and kept my attention when I was a newbie because his visuals also made it easier to remember him haha. And I’m pretty sure a lot of other ARMYs can agree to this. So yes, I’m definitely putting him in the unique list here.    That’s it :) Thanks for reading. Appreciate these unique visuals and all other visuals in K-Pop :D
